This program allows you to edit some settings of the "server.exe"... I will explain the settings shortly, but first you have to select the "server.exe" by clicking on the "select server" button, or just type the full path...
after you did that you're able to change the settings.
Filename after *installation* is the name that the server will get when it's extracted to the system-directory. Example: "server.exe".
Main port: This is the port to use to connect to the server...must be a number between 1 and 65535.
Keylog port: This port will be used when you activate the keylogger...must be a number between 1 and 65535, but make sure it's not the same as the main or transfer port.
Transfer port: Same as the "Keylog port", but this port is used for file-transfer.
Password: You can password protect the server to overcome connections of other "Net-Devil-users", when you connect to the server you will be prompted to enter the password.

To make the server start every windows-boot, an entry has to be created in the registry... "Run" and "RunServices" are the possibilities. Also you have to enter a name which will be used in the registry. Can be everything... but make sure it's not too obvious like "Trojan".
